    "answer_id" : 33540048,
    "question_id" : 2800739,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>If you don't want to use regex or external library.\nYou can do with \"for\": </p>\n\n<pre><code>String input=\"0000008008451\"\nString output = input.trim();\nfor( ;output.length() &gt; 1 &amp;&amp; output.charAt(0) == '0'; output = output.substring(1));\n\nSystem.out.println(output);//8008451\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
