    "question_id" : 2800739,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>And what about just searching for the first non-zero character?</p>\n\n<pre><code>[1-9]\\d+\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>This regex finds the first digit between 1 and 9 followed by any number of digits, so for <strong>\"00012345\"</strong> it returns <strong>\"12345\"</strong>.\nIt can be easily adapted for alphanumeric strings.</p>\n"
  }, {
