  "title" : "How to remove leading zeros from alphanumeric text?",
  "body" : "<p>I've seen questions on how to prefix zeros here in SO. But not the other way!</p>\n\n<p>Can you guys suggest me how to remove the leading zeros in alphanumeric text? Are there any built-in APIs or do I need to write a method to trim the leading zeros?</p>\n\n<p>Example:</p>\n\n<pre><code>01234 converts to 1234\n0001234a converts to 1234a\n001234-a converts to 1234-a\n101234 remains as 101234\n2509398 remains as 2509398\n123z remains as 123z\n000002829839 converts to 2829839\n</code></pre>\n"
